"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-18-CMG-preparing-to-provide-first-class-reports-on-2024-Paris-Olympics-1vkth64wBXy-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Sports Scene  Copied  Members of the China Media Group's working staff prepare for the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris. /CMG  The China Media Group (CMG), as one of the primary broadcasters for the upcoming 2024 Summer Olympics, has dispatched a production and broadcasting team of more than 2,000 people to Paris.  The frontline staff have been setting up a working area of over 1,500 square meters at the International Broadcast Centre (IBC) in the French capital since mid-June, with a transcontinental Olympic broadcasting cloud platform based on CMG's media cloud established to provide various production tools including video, audio, picture and text editing, merging and packaging.  CMG began to set up its ultra-high-definition broadcasting system at the location shooting site and television studio at the Eiffel Tower and IBC on July 3. The construction work is expected to be completed by Saturday.  CMG will deploy nearly 40 media convergence groups at different venues during the 2024 Summer Olympics, ready to provide first-class, professional reports to its audience through a series of premium programs.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"